data.text: @adamksmet true. Thought the same thing, just couldn't articulate it as well.
@FrayedBlueJeans I wasn't a huge fan of the final ep, but I liked that ep 9 was basically a  finale & goodbye while ep 10 was an epilogue for the character.
@FrayedBlueJeans Agreed. I thought having them grow apart & separate was a bold move for a show that was based around their friendships. Very fitting though.
@adamksmet was fun to see them growing up this season, bittersweet watching them grow apart to an extent.
@adamksmet true. Last week's episode was great. The actual finale was a bit anticlimactic but very Lena Dunham-Girls-like.
@FrayedBlueJeans What a final season. The storytelling through me for a loop so many times, left me quite surprised at times. Such a bold way to end the show
